Description=Website: https://www.wch.cn/products/CH32V407.html?\nROM(byte): 512K, SRAM(byte): 200K, CHIP PINS: 64, GPIO PORTS: 49.\nThe CH32V407 is an industrial-grade interconnect microcontroller based on the barley RISC-V core. It supports a 200 MHz main frequency with zero wait state operation and the V vector instruction set, and is used for accelerating computations or parallel processing applications. The CH32V407 is equipped with 2 sets of USB 2.0 high-speed PHY transceivers (480 Mbps), an Ethernet MAC controller, and 10/100 Mbps physical layer transceivers; it also includes two ADC units, two DAC units, and OPA amplifiers as analog resources; it provides 2 sets of a total of 24 DMA controllers, SDIO, DVP digital image interface, RNG, ARGB, LTDC, FSMC, multiple timers, 10 USART serial ports, I2C interface, I3C interface, 3 SPI interfaces, 2 I2S interfaces, and CAN interfaces, offering a rich set of peripheral resources.The CH32V467, based on the CH32V407, adds 4M or 8M bytes of on-chip expanded PSRAM memory and supports DMA.
